The paper proposes a data-driven model for project selection process using historical datasets and evidential reasoning. This involves utilizing experimental data, combining multiple pieces of evidence, and taking experts' reliabilities into account. These concepts are closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also discusses the use of historical statistics and data-driven approaches, which are relevant to social and information sciences (cs.SI) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the fairness and interpretability of the selection process, which is related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and ethics in AI.
